13. The method according to claim 12, wherein the second plant is a stevia plant with high rebaudioside M content ratio having at least one of the following genetic features (1) and (2), and at least one of the following genetic features (3) to (7):
(1) homozygous for the allele wherein the base at the position corresponding to position 290 of SEQ ID NO: 1 is T;
(2) homozygous for the allele wherein the base at the position corresponding to position 33 of SEQ ID NO: 2 is A;
(3) homozygous for the allele wherein the base at the position corresponding to position 44 of SEQ ID NO: 3 is T;
(4) homozygous for the allele wherein the base at the position corresponding to position 40 of SEQ ID NO: 4 is T;
(5) homozygous for the allele wherein the base at the position corresponding to position 48 of SEQ ID NO: 5 is C;
(6) homozygous for the allele wherein the portion corresponding to positions 55-72 of SEQ ID NO: 6 is deleted; and
(7) homozygous for the allele wherein the base at the position corresponding to position 50 of SEQ ID NO: 7 is A.
